cs.PL, cs.LO, cs.SE, cs.TY, cs.DS 

This paper deals with type systems and verification, which are typically studied in the programming languages (cs.PL) and logic (cs.LO) sub-categories. It also discusses well-formedness and separate compilation, which are relevant to software engineering (cs.SE). The paper specifically focuses on refinement types for inductive datatypes, which falls under the type theory (cs.TY) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses signature extensions, which are related to data structures (cs.DS).
